# Crawler outputs. Re-creatable by running:
#   python3 scripts/fcdo_treaties_crawl.py --resume
#
# The per-treaty JSON in records/ and the rolled-up all.nq.gz are
# always committed. The html/ fragments are partially committed:
# small fragments (the country/action/date tables, ~1 KB each) ARE
# committed so an LLM verifier can audit the extractor against the
# same source bytes; only files >= 1 MB (PDF-like blobs that gov.uk
# serves at the same URL for some treaties) are excluded -- they
# compress poorly and are not the source of any extracted triple.
# A .gitattributes filter would be more elegant, but per-file size
# filtering at the gitignore level isn't supported, so the rule lives
# in fcdo_treaties_crawl.py instead: small files go to html/, large
# ones go to html/large/ which is the path actually ignored.

html/large/
crawl.log
extractors/factoids/*.ttl
!extractors/factoids/parliament-bridge.ttl
extractors/factoids/all.nq
